"content":[{"value":"[Box on EAG platform]"}]}]},{"type":"section","id":"section-d1e147","content":[{"type":"section","id":"section-d1e148","content":[{"type":"sectiontitle2","id":"heading-d1e149","content":[{"value":"Comparability and interpretation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e160","align":"justify","content":[{"type":"emphasis","id":"d1e245","emph":"italic","content":[{"value":"The indicators used in this report are of varying relevance for different countries. Care should be taken when interpreting the indicators and when making international comparisons: "}]}]},{"type":"randlist","id":"d1e247","content":[{"type":"randlistitem","id":"d1e248","label":"","content":[{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e165","content":[{"type":"emphasis","id":"d1e250","emph":"italic","content":[{"value":"National averages can mask significant variations within countries. l Definitions and measurement methods vary among countries, hence inter-country comparisons may not compare the same things."}]}]}]},{"type":"randlistitem","id":"d1e252","label":"","content":[{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e171","content":[{"type":"emphasis","id":"d1e254","emph":"italic","content":[{"value":"There is a level of uncertainty associated with the data sources and measurement methods on which the indicators rely. Differences between two countries’ indicators are thus not always statistically significant; and when countries are clustered around a relatively narrow range of outcomes, it may be misleading to establish an order of ranking. "}]}]}]},{"type":"randlistitem","id":"d1e256","label":"","content":[{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e177","content":[{"type":"emphasis","id":"d1e258","emph":"italic","content":[{"value":"No single approach has been used for normalising the indicators; different denominators are used in parallel to balance the message conveyed. Many indicators are expressed on a per capita and per unit of GDP basis. The population estimates used include persons who are resident in a country for one year or more, regardless of their citizenship. The GDP figures used are expressed in USD and in 2010 prices and purchasing power parities (PPPs). Definitions and metadata can be found in the webbooks available at http://www.oecd.org/environment/ environment-at-a-glance/. "}]}]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"section","id":"section-d1e183","content":[{"type":"section","id":"section-d1e184","content":[{"type":"sectiontitle2","id":"heading-d1e185","content":[{"value":"Cut-off date"}]},{"type":"paragraph","id":"p-d1e196","align":"justify","content":[{"type":"emphasis","id":"d1e266","emph":"italic","content":[{"value":"The indicators build on the latest available data from OECD and other international sources up to January 2023. Some indicators draw on recent work carried out under the IPAC xxxx."}]}]}]}]}],"pagesInfo":[{"id":"foreword-d1e83","title":"Foreword"},{"id":"execsumm-d1e106","title":"Executive Summary"},{"id":"introduction-d4e93","title":"Reader’s guide"},{"id":"chapter-d1e200","title":"Introduction"},{"id":"chapter-d1e540","title":"Climate change "},{"id":"chapter-d1e1439","title":"Air quality "},{"id":"chapter-d1e1818","title":"Biodiversity "},{"id":"chapter-d1e2195","title":"Environmental policy instruments"},{"id":"chapter-d1e2505","title":"Glossary"},{"id":"chapter-d1e2992","title":"Data sources"}],"lang":"en","sdgs":null,"keywordLabel":"","keywords":null,"countries":null,"regions":null,"otherLanguage":null,"relatedProduct":null,"relatedPublication":[],"relatedContent":[],"relatedWebsite":[],"toc":[{"type":"toctitle","id":"toctitle","content":[{"value":"Table of contents"}]},{"value":"Environment at a Glance Indicators: Latin America and Caribbean (LAC) provides interactive on-line access to the latest comparable LAC-country data on the environment. The tool helps users evaluate environmental performance in the region’s countries and track their course towards sustainable development. This web version allows users to play with the data, dive into the analysis 